<i>Just fight it out</i>

50
00:02:58,317 --> 00:03:00,275
<i>Just fight it out</i>

51
00:03:04,025 --> 00:03:08,983
[FILO humming]

52
00:03:32,650 --> 00:03:34,483
[RAPHTALIA] If we could
just get past that wall,

53
00:03:34,567 --> 00:03:36,942
we'd be on the other
side of the border.

54
00:03:37,025 --> 00:03:39,650
[MELTY] Are there any other
routes we could take, Raphtalia?

55
00:03:39,733 --> 00:03:41,233
[RAPHTALIA]
Hmm...

56
00:03:41,317 --> 00:03:42,733
We could take a detour,

57
00:03:42,817 --> 00:03:45,900
but if we do, it'll cost us
a few more days on the road.

58
00:03:45,983 --> 00:03:48,233
Yes, but Fitoria said
there was another hero

59
00:03:48,317 --> 00:03:50,608
not too far from
here, didn't she?

60
00:03:50,692 --> 00:03:54,192
It might make sense for us
to take that detour anyway.

61
00:03:54,275 --> 00:03:55,567
[RAPHTALIA]
Master Naofumi?

62
00:03:55,650 --> 00:03:57,650
What do you think?

63
00:03:57,733 --> 00:04:00,733
Did you ever really try to
make up with the other heroes?

64
00:04:00,817 --> 00:04:02,692
If you don't tell them
they're wrong about you,

65
00:04:02,775 --> 00:04:05,608
they'll take it as an
admission of your guilt.

66
00:04:05,692 --> 00:04:08,567
Don't forget--
you made me a promise.

67
00:04:11,150 --> 00:04:13,192
We'll head straight
to the checkpoint.

68
00:04:13,275 --> 00:04:16,817
If it's Itsuki or Ren, we might
be able to persuade them.

69
00:04:16,900 --> 00:04:18,025
Okay.

70
00:04:18,108 --> 00:04:20,358
But what do we do if
that doesn't work?

71
00:04:20,442 --> 00:04:23,192
[NAOFUMI] We'll just have
to force our way through.

72
00:04:23,275 --> 00:04:24,567
[MELTY]
All right, then.

73
00:04:24,650 --> 00:04:25,858
[NAOFUMI gasps]

74
00:04:27,067 --> 00:04:27,983
What is it?

75
00:04:28,067 --> 00:04:29,317
[NAOFUMI]
Well...

76
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:31,400
I figured you'd try to
stop me from doing anything

77
00:04:31,483 --> 00:04:33,233
that'd make my reputation worse.

78
00:04:33,317 --> 00:04:34,733
There are men out
there, like Idol,

79
00:04:34,817 --> 00:04:36,358
who are willing to
summon monsters

80
00:04:36,442 --> 00:04:38,733
just so they can
torment innocent people.

81
00:04:38,817 --> 00:04:42,025
This isn't the time to be
worried about your reputation.

82
00:04:42,108 --> 00:04:43,900
[NAOFUMI]
You make a good point.

83
00:04:43,983 --> 00:04:44,983
Uh?

84
00:04:45,067 --> 00:04:46,942
[NAOFUMI]
Get ready. We're leaving.

85
00:04:47,025 --> 00:04:48,567
--[RAPHTALIA] All right!
--[FILO] Okie-dokie!

86
00:04:54,192 --> 00:04:55,942
[gasps] I-Is that...?

87
00:04:59,608 --> 00:05:04,858
[horn blows]

88
00:05:07,275 --> 00:05:09,400
Hey, Master, look!

89
00:05:09,483 --> 00:05:11,942
It's that spear guy again.

90
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:14,567
It just had to be the guy

91
00:05:14,650 --> 00:05:17,108
that was least likely
to listen to me, huh?

92
00:05:17,192 --> 00:05:18,692
What do we do now?

93
00:05:18,775 --> 00:05:20,567
[NAOFUMI]
It's too late to turn back.

94
00:05:20,650 --> 00:05:22,358
We have to keep going.

95
00:05:27,483 --> 00:05:30,358
[NAOFUMI]
Motoyasu. I wanna talk.

96
00:05:30,442 --> 00:05:33,358
We're not here to
start a fight with you.

97
00:05:33,442 --> 00:05:36,608
All we're asking is
that you let us through.

98
00:05:36,692 --> 00:05:39,275
"Let you through,"
huh? Is that all?

99
00:05:39,358 --> 00:05:40,692
[NAOFUMI]
Huh?

100
00:05:40,775 --> 00:05:42,858
Is that all you have
to say for yourself?!

101
00:05:42,942 --> 00:05:43,817
Traitor!

102
00:05:43,900 --> 00:05:46,025
Devil of the Shield!

103
00:05:46,108 --> 00:05:47,192
[NAOFUMI grunts]

104
00:05:49,983 --> 00:05:51,150
Master Naofumi!

105
00:05:51,233 --> 00:05:52,525
Can't you at least listen to me

106
00:05:52,608 --> 00:05:54,567
before you try to
take my head off?

107
00:05:54,650 --> 00:05:56,275
I won't listen to
anyone who uses

108
00:05:56,358 --> 00:06:00,442
a brainwashing shield to
enslave Filo and Raphtalia.

109
00:06:00,525 --> 00:06:02,108
You're despicable!

110
00:06:02,192 --> 00:06:03,567
They aren't brainwashed!

111
00:06:03,650 --> 00:06:06,275
[MOTOYASU] Don't even try to
talk your way out of this!

112
00:06:06,358 --> 00:06:07,858
[groans]

113
00:06:07,942 --> 00:06:11,525
[FITORIA] The Cardinal Heroes
are supposed to work together.

114
00:06:11,608 --> 00:06:14,900
[groans] Dammit, Motoyasu,
just hear me out!

115
00:06:14,983 --> 00:06:16,567
I don't want to fight you!

116
00:06:16,650 --> 00:06:17,858
Hell, last time
I didn't want to--

117
00:06:17,942 --> 00:06:20,567
I finally know the reason
I was summoned here.

118
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:25,025
I think I might be here
specifically to stop you!

119
00:06:25,108 --> 00:06:26,233
[gasps]

120
00:06:26,317 --> 00:06:28,442
[MOTOYASU]
Meteor Thrust!

121
00:06:30,442 --> 00:06:31,692
[NAOFUMI grunts]

122
00:06:33,233 --> 00:06:34,567
[NAOFUMI grunting]

123
00:06:34,650 --> 00:06:36,567
[ALL grunting]

124
00:06:41,775 --> 00:06:44,400
[NAOFUMI panting]

125
00:06:44,483 --> 00:06:46,317
You're still not down yet?

126
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:47,733
You sure are stubborn.

127
00:06:47,817 --> 00:06:48,900
I'll give you that.

128
00:06:48,983 --> 00:06:52,108
Come on, Master,
let me at him! [growls]

129
00:06:52,192 --> 00:06:53,358
If that's his attitude,

130
00:06:53,442 --> 00:06:55,608
nothing you say is going
to get through to him!

131
00:06:55,692 --> 00:06:57,442
[NAOFUMI]
She's right.

132
00:06:57,525 --> 00:06:59,608
Why is he doing this?

133
00:07:01,192 --> 00:07:03,108
Hey, Motoyasu.

134
00:07:03,192 --> 00:07:05,775
Why exactly are you
so mad at me?

135
00:07:05,858 --> 00:07:08,567
Is it because I ran away
last time we fought?

136
00:07:09,692 --> 00:07:12,108
[MOTOYASU]
Are you that heartless?

137
00:07:12,192 --> 00:07:15,775
Were Ren and Itsuki
that insignificant to you?!

138
00:07:15,858 --> 00:07:17,775
People call you the devil.

139
00:07:17,858 --> 00:07:20,233
Now I finally understand!

140
00:07:20,317 --> 00:07:21,483
Huh?

141
00:07:21,567 --> 00:07:22,858
[MOTOYASU]
You told us the heroes should be

142
00:07:22,942 --> 00:07:24,358
on the same team.

143
00:07:24,442 --> 00:07:25,817
You tricked us!

144
00:07:25,900 --> 00:07:27,942
We trusted you...

145
00:07:28,025 --> 00:07:30,317
You bastard!

146
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:32,233
I'm gonna make you pay!

147
00:07:32,317 --> 00:07:33,275
[NAOFUMI grunts]

148
00:07:35,983 --> 00:07:37,192
You're done!

149
00:07:37,275 --> 00:07:38,067
I'll make sure of it!

150
00:07:38,150 --> 00:07:39,400
[NAOFUMI grunts]

151
00:07:39,483 --> 00:07:41,733
Hey! I don't even know
what it is you think I did!

152
00:07:41,817 --> 00:07:42,858
Well, you should.

153
00:07:42,942 --> 00:07:44,317
Think about it!

154
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:46,817
[NAOFUMI] He's seriously
trying to kill me!

155
00:07:47,817 --> 00:07:49,067
--[NAOFUMI grunts]
--[MOTOYASU growls]

156
00:07:49,150 --> 00:07:51,275
You're gonna pay.

157
00:07:51,358 --> 00:07:53,608
You're gonna pay for
what you did to them!

158
00:07:53,692 --> 00:07:55,942
Murderer!

159
00:07:56,025 --> 00:07:57,442
[NAOFUMI gasps]

160
00:08:00,483 --> 00:08:01,525
[NAOFUMI]
Murderer?

161
00:08:01,608 --> 00:08:03,483
What do mean? Who's dead?!

162
00:08:03,567 --> 00:08:06,525
Don't play dumb with me.
You know what you did!

163
00:08:06,608 --> 00:08:07,400
[grunts]

164
00:08:10,817 --> 00:08:12,108
How can you stand
there and pretend

165
00:08:12,192 --> 00:08:14,275
you don't understand
why I'm so angry?

166
00:08:14,358 --> 00:08:16,692
You might as well admit it.
You killed them!

167
00:08:16,775 --> 00:08:19,608
And yet... here you are.

168
00:08:19,692 --> 00:08:21,692
The heroes of the Bow
and Sword were killed?

169
00:08:21,775 --> 00:08:22,858
How could this have happened?

170
00:08:22,942 --> 00:08:24,525
Both of them were so strong!

171
00:08:24,608 --> 00:08:25,942
[gasps]

172
00:08:26,025 --> 00:08:28,733
You used your brainwashing
shield on Princess Melty?

173
00:08:28,817 --> 00:08:30,317
You'll do anything, won't you?!

174
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:32,983
I'm not brainwashing anyone!

175
00:08:33,067 --> 00:08:36,150
[NAOFUMI] If what Motoyasu's
saying is true...

176
00:08:36,233 --> 00:08:37,317
You need to understand that

177
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:39,525
if even one Cardinal
Hero is missing,

178
00:08:39,608 --> 00:08:43,108
fighting off a Wave
becomes almost impossible.

179
00:08:43,192 --> 00:08:45,775
Now I really need you
to listen to me.

180
00:08:45,858 --> 00:08:47,942
I didn't kill Ren or Itsuki!

181
00:08:48,025 --> 00:08:49,525
Why would I wanna do that?

182
00:08:49,608 --> 00:08:50,442
What do you mean?

183
00:08:50,525 --> 00:08:51,650
[NAOFUMI]
Tell me this--

184
00:08:51,733 --> 00:08:53,400
did you see their bodies
with your own eyes?

185
00:08:53,483 --> 00:08:54,317
[MOTOYASU grunts]

186
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:55,983
I'll take that as a no.

187
00:08:56,067 --> 00:08:57,192
So maybe somebody's lying--

188
00:08:57,275 --> 00:08:58,942
[MYNE] I think a
representative of the Church

189
00:08:59,025 --> 00:09:00,608
is a reliable source.

190
00:09:00,692 --> 00:09:02,150
They said the
Devil of the Shield

191
00:09:02,233 --> 00:09:04,942
unleashed a monster sealed
in the center of town.

192
00:09:05,025 --> 00:09:07,150
Then you used the devastation
as a distraction

193
00:09:07,233 --> 00:09:09,192
to kill Itsuki and Ren.

194
00:09:09,275 --> 00:09:11,067
--[NAOFUMI groans]
--Ridiculous!

195
00:09:11,150 --> 00:09:14,608
Sir Motoyasu, beware of
his brainwashing shield.

196
00:09:14,692 --> 00:09:17,567
You can't let the devil
sway you with his words.

197
00:09:17,650 --> 00:09:19,525
No need to worry about that.

198
00:09:19,608 --> 00:09:21,608
He can't fool me!

199
00:09:21,692 --> 00:09:24,483
I don't understand why
she's always like this.

200
00:09:26,192 --> 00:09:27,442
What do you think?

201
00:09:27,525 --> 00:09:29,317
Oh, no, Sister... You didn't...

202
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:32,567
[NAOFUMI gasps] You're the one
who killed them, aren't you?!

203
00:09:32,650 --> 00:09:35,442
Enough chitchat.
It's time to battle!

204
00:09:44,608 --> 00:09:45,442
[RAPHTALIA]
What is this?

205
00:09:45,525 --> 00:09:47,650
You're using a Lightning Cage?!

206
00:09:47,733 --> 00:09:49,775
An impenetrable prison
made of lightning,

207
00:09:49,858 --> 00:09:51,733
sealing in the caster
and her target

208
00:09:51,817 --> 00:09:53,900
until one of them can
subdue the other.

209
00:09:53,983 --> 00:09:55,608
You won't get away this time!

210
00:09:55,692 --> 00:09:58,108
I swear that I will
avenge their deaths!

211
00:09:58,192 --> 00:10:00,692
Take it easy and think
this through, all right?

212
00:10:00,775 --> 00:10:02,567
Are you going to believe
everything they say

213
00:10:02,650 --> 00:10:04,025
without confirming it?

214
00:10:04,108 --> 00:10:05,400
There's no need.

215
00:10:05,483 --> 00:10:06,733
My friends are
trustworthy enough

216
00:10:06,817 --> 00:10:08,358
to take them at their word!

217
00:10:08,442 --> 00:10:10,108
[NAOFUMI]
This guy's an idiot.

218
00:10:10,192 --> 00:10:12,858
She's got him dancing
in the palm of her hand!

219
00:10:12,942 --> 00:10:14,358
--[MOTOYASU] You're finished!
--[NAOFUMI gasps]

220
00:10:14,442 --> 00:10:17,025
[MOTOYASU yells]

221
00:10:17,817 --> 00:10:19,942
[groans, grunts]

222
00:10:20,025 --> 00:10:21,483
[MOTOYASU groans]

223
00:10:21,567 --> 00:10:23,108
Shield Prison!

224
00:10:29,150 --> 00:10:31,858
[NAOFUMI gasps] His level's
much higher than mine!

225
00:10:31,942 --> 00:10:33,108
Filo, go!

226
00:10:33,192 --> 00:10:35,317
[FILO]
All right!

227
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:36,983
[MYNE]
Oh, no, you don't.

228
00:10:37,067 --> 00:10:40,733
As source of thy power and as
the next queen, I order thee.

229
00:10:40,817 --> 00:10:43,650
How pretentious can
an incantation get?

230
00:10:43,733 --> 00:10:46,817
Decipher the laws of creation
and bring down a rain of fire

231
00:10:46,900 --> 00:10:49,025
that will consume
all of my targets!

232
00:10:49,108 --> 00:10:51,817
Zweit Fire Squall!

233
00:10:55,942 --> 00:10:58,150
I order thee to nullify
the rain of fire

234
00:10:58,233 --> 00:11:00,650
and keep my targets
safe from its flames!

235
00:11:00,733 --> 00:11:03,775
Anti-Zweit Fire Squall!

236
00:11:05,567 --> 00:11:06,858
[MELTY]
Naofumi!

237
00:11:06,942 --> 00:11:08,358
Okay, Filo, you ready?

238
00:11:08,442 --> 00:11:09,692
You bet!

239
00:11:11,650 --> 00:11:12,483
[FILO grunts]

240
00:11:12,567 --> 00:11:14,317
[FILO yells]

241
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:15,275
[MOTOYASU groans]

242
00:11:15,358 --> 00:11:16,692
Not so fast!

243
00:11:16,775 --> 00:11:19,358
Zweit Air Shot!

244
00:11:22,275 --> 00:11:23,442
[FILO gasps]

245
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:28,067
[MOTOYASU grunts]

246
00:11:28,150 --> 00:11:30,192
[FILO grunts, yells]

247
00:11:32,275 --> 00:11:33,650
--[FILO grunts]
--[MOTOYASU groans]

248
00:11:33,733 --> 00:11:35,150
[MOTOYASU gasps]

249
00:11:35,233 --> 00:11:36,567
--[FILO yells]
--[MOTOYASU groans]

250
00:11:36,650 --> 00:11:38,233
Amazing!

251
00:11:38,317 --> 00:11:41,192
That's the move she learned
during her duel with Fitoria.

252
00:11:41,275 --> 00:11:43,733
She's making good use of it!

253
00:11:43,817 --> 00:11:45,233
Forgive me for this, Filo,

254
00:11:45,317 --> 00:11:47,733
but I must fight for Ren and
Itsuki, no matter the cost,

255
00:11:47,817 --> 00:11:49,942
even if it means
I have to hurt you.

256
00:11:51,275 --> 00:11:53,442
[MOTOYASU yells]

257
00:12:01,650 --> 00:12:04,192
[MOTOYASU]
Meteor Thrust!

258
00:12:08,567 --> 00:12:10,275
I'm not done!

259
00:12:10,358 --> 00:12:11,983
Chaos Spear!

260
00:12:12,067 --> 00:12:13,525
[NAOFUMI grunts]

261
00:12:13,608 --> 00:12:15,358
Myne! Now's our chance!

262
00:12:15,442 --> 00:12:17,150
Zweit Fire!

263
00:12:17,233 --> 00:12:19,233
[ADVENTURER 18A, 18B]
Zweit Air Shot!

264
00:12:23,108 --> 00:12:24,983
Behold the power
of a combo skill

265
00:12:25,067 --> 00:12:27,233
with fire, wind, and my spear!

266
00:12:27,317 --> 00:12:28,275
[gasps]

267
00:12:29,317 --> 00:12:31,858
[MOTOYASU]
Air-Burst Flare Lance!

268
00:12:34,733 --> 00:12:39,400
[NAOFUMI groaning]

269
00:12:39,483 --> 00:12:41,233
Master Naofumi!

270
00:12:41,317 --> 00:12:44,108
Zweit Air Shot!

271
00:12:44,192 --> 00:12:46,150
Zweit Aqua Shot!

272
00:12:48,567 --> 00:12:49,317
[ADVENTURER 18A yelps]

273
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:50,692
Melty.

274
00:12:51,733 --> 00:12:53,192
Are you all right?

275
00:12:55,150 --> 00:12:56,150
[NAOFUMI]
Hold on...

276
00:12:56,233 --> 00:12:57,817
That's a combo skill?

277
00:12:57,900 --> 00:12:59,233
Huh?

278
00:12:59,317 --> 00:13:01,317
We can do what they just did!

279
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:02,483
You ready?

280
00:13:02,567 --> 00:13:03,358
Okay.

281
00:13:03,442 --> 00:13:04,567
[MOTOYASU]
Raphtalia!

282
00:13:04,650 --> 00:13:05,817
--[RAPHTALIA] Hm?
--[NAOFUMI gasps]

283
00:13:05,900 --> 00:13:07,608
[MOTOYASU] If you continue
to take his side,

284
00:13:07,692 --> 00:13:09,817
I can't show you any mercy.

285
00:13:09,900 --> 00:13:12,733
As source of thy power,
I order thee.

286
00:13:12,817 --> 00:13:16,400
Decipher the laws of
nature and hide my target.

287
00:13:16,483 --> 00:13:18,400
First Hiding!

288
00:13:18,483 --> 00:13:20,025
[NAOFUMI]
Hiding Shield!

289
00:13:25,817 --> 00:13:27,567
--[gasps]
--[NAOFUMI] Change Shield!

290
00:13:29,608 --> 00:13:30,650
[MOTOYASU yells]

291
00:13:32,192 --> 00:13:32,942
[MOTOYASU groans]

292
00:13:33,025 --> 00:13:33,942
Sir Motoyasu!

293
00:13:34,025 --> 00:13:36,733
[MOTOYASU groaning]

294
00:13:39,567 --> 00:13:41,900
[MOTOYASU] He just stole
my skill points from me!

295
00:13:41,983 --> 00:13:44,775
You really think that's
gonna help you beat me?

296
00:13:44,858 --> 00:13:45,650
[NAOFUMI grunts]

297
00:13:45,733 --> 00:13:47,608
I don't need to use any skills!

298
00:13:47,692 --> 00:13:48,900
[NAOFUMI]
Filo!

299
00:13:48,983 --> 00:13:50,358
High Quick!

300
00:13:51,733 --> 00:13:53,983
[MOTOYASU yells]

301
00:13:54,067 --> 00:13:55,817
Oh, no, Sir Motoyasu!

302
00:13:55,900 --> 00:13:56,692
[RAPHTALIA]
Wide open.

303
00:13:56,775 --> 00:13:58,150
[gasps]

304
00:13:58,233 --> 00:13:58,983
[grunts]

305
00:13:59,067 --> 00:14:00,358
[MYNE gasps]

306
00:14:00,442 --> 00:14:02,650
[RAPHTALIA] You won't get
in Master Naofumi's way!

307
00:14:02,733 --> 00:14:07,525
[MYNE groans] You dare to
strike me, you damn demi-human?

308
00:14:07,608 --> 00:14:08,942
I'll get you!

309
00:14:09,025 --> 00:14:11,942
How can you force poor Raphtalia
and sweet little Filo

310
00:14:12,025 --> 00:14:13,067
to fight for you?

311
00:14:13,150 --> 00:14:14,900
[NAOFUMI]
Still don't get it, do you?

312
00:14:14,983 --> 00:14:15,900
Get what?

313
00:14:15,983 --> 00:14:18,192
Filo! Melty!

314
00:14:18,275 --> 00:14:21,067
As source of thy power,
we order thee!

315
00:14:21,150 --> 00:14:25,358
Decipher the laws of nature
and bring forth a raging wind!

316
00:14:25,442 --> 00:14:29,733
Bring forth torrential rain--
a downpour like no other!

317
00:14:29,817 --> 00:14:32,567
[MELTY, FILO] Create a storm
to blow our targets away!

318
00:14:32,650 --> 00:14:34,733
Typhoon!

319
00:14:37,317 --> 00:14:38,067
[MOTOYASU yells]

320
00:14:38,150 --> 00:14:40,025
[MYNE, ADVENTURERS yell]

321
00:14:41,858 --> 00:14:43,150
--[FILO giggles]
--Nice work, Filo!

322
00:14:43,233 --> 00:14:44,483
We make a great team!

323
00:14:44,567 --> 00:14:46,067
We do!

324
00:14:49,525 --> 00:14:51,275
[ALL groan]

325
00:14:51,358 --> 00:14:52,483
Damn...

326
00:14:52,567 --> 00:14:54,317
You haven't upgraded your class.

327
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:56,483
How can you possibly
be this strong?

328
00:14:56,567 --> 00:14:59,192
Does the brainwashing shield
make you more powerful, too?

329
00:14:59,275 --> 00:15:00,400
[NAOFUMI] While you and
your party have been

330
00:15:00,483 --> 00:15:02,275
having fun playing superheroes,

331
00:15:02,358 --> 00:15:03,775
we've been out here
doing the grunt work

332
00:15:03,858 --> 00:15:06,400
to clean up after you
and acquire new skills.

333
00:15:06,483 --> 00:15:07,983
Liar!

334
00:15:08,067 --> 00:15:10,525
Do you honestly expect me to
believe it's as simple as that?

335
00:15:10,608 --> 00:15:12,692
[NAOFUMI] Believe it
or not, it's the truth.

336
00:15:13,608 --> 00:15:14,983
[NAOFUMI]
We do what we have to do,

337
00:15:15,067 --> 00:15:17,567
no matter how
trivial it may seem.

338
00:15:17,650 --> 00:15:19,442
That's why you lost to us.

339
00:15:19,525 --> 00:15:20,608
I... [groans]

340
00:15:20,692 --> 00:15:22,400
[NAOFUMI]
Give it a rest, Motoyasu.

341
00:15:22,483 --> 00:15:24,983
It's your turn to listen to me!

342
00:15:25,067 --> 00:15:26,442
Doesn't matter...

343
00:15:26,525 --> 00:15:29,150
It doesn't matter
what you have to say.

344
00:15:29,233 --> 00:15:31,567
I've got to avenge
Itsuki and Ren.

345
00:15:31,650 --> 00:15:33,025
If I give up,

346
00:15:33,108 --> 00:15:36,358
Raphtalia, Princess Melty,
and Filo will never be free!

347
00:15:36,442 --> 00:15:39,733
They'll always be the Devil
of the Shield's prisoners!

348
00:15:39,817 --> 00:15:41,775
And I can never accept that!

349
00:15:41,858 --> 00:15:43,942
Not as long as I live.

350
00:15:44,025 --> 00:15:45,775
'Cause I'm the Spear Hero!

351
00:15:45,858 --> 00:15:48,983
That's Sir Motoyasu.
Fight until the end!

352
00:15:49,067 --> 00:15:51,025
Bring me the Devil
of the Shield's head

353
00:15:51,108 --> 00:15:54,567
and free my dear sister,
Melty, from his clutches!

354
00:15:54,650 --> 00:15:55,650
[MOTOYASU grunts]

355
00:15:56,983 --> 00:15:58,483
[NAOFUMI] How am I
ever gonna get through

356
00:15:58,567 --> 00:16:01,900
to this thickheaded moron when
he's got a damn hero complex?

357
00:16:01,983 --> 00:16:02,733
[FILO gasps]

358
00:16:02,817 --> 00:16:04,567
What is it, Filo?

359
00:16:04,650 --> 00:16:06,442
[RAPHTALIA gasps]

360
00:16:06,525 --> 00:16:08,067
Something's off...

361
00:16:08,150 --> 00:16:10,733
Look--all the soldiers
have left their posts.

362
00:16:16,858 --> 00:16:18,650
[FILO gasps]

363
00:16:18,733 --> 00:16:19,942
[ADVENTURER 18B yelps]

364
00:16:20,025 --> 00:16:21,317
[ADVENTURER 18A gasps]

365
00:16:21,400 --> 00:16:22,358
[MYNE yelps]

366
00:16:22,442 --> 00:16:24,483
[ADVENTURERS, MOTOYASU, MYNE
groan]

367
00:16:24,567 --> 00:16:26,067
What was that all about, Filo?

368
00:16:26,150 --> 00:16:28,317
Master! Bring out the
dark shield, quick!

369
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:30,483
And a bunch of
other shields, too!

370
00:16:30,567 --> 00:16:32,775
If you don't, then all
of us are done for!

371
00:16:32,858 --> 00:16:34,025
There's no time to waste!

372
00:16:34,108 --> 00:16:35,567
What are you talking about?

373
00:16:35,650 --> 00:16:38,233
Hurry up! Do it! Now!

374
00:16:38,317 --> 00:16:39,358
[BOTH]
Mm.

375
00:16:41,108 --> 00:16:42,983
Shield Prison!

376
00:16:46,108 --> 00:16:48,025
[FILO]
We need more!

377
00:16:48,108 --> 00:16:49,692
Up above!

378
00:16:49,775 --> 00:16:52,067
Air Strike Shield!

379
00:16:52,150 --> 00:16:53,900
Second Shield!

380
00:16:56,317 --> 00:16:58,692
What in the world is
going on here anyway?

381
00:16:58,775 --> 00:17:00,483
Shut your mouth for once!

382
00:17:00,567 --> 00:17:02,108
[FILO]
Here it comes!

383
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:13,025
[ALL scream]

384
00:17:28,317 --> 00:17:33,275
[NAOFUMI yelling]

385
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:39,192
[NAOFUMI yelling]

386
00:18:02,900 --> 00:18:06,733
[NAOFUMI groans, pants]

387
00:18:06,817 --> 00:18:07,942
[RAPHTALIA gasps]

388
00:18:09,817 --> 00:18:11,150
Are you all right?

389
00:18:12,192 --> 00:18:14,025
Filo and Melty?

390
00:18:14,108 --> 00:18:15,442
We're fine!

391
00:18:15,525 --> 00:18:16,942
[MOTOYASU]
What was that?

392
00:18:18,192 --> 00:18:20,608
Myne, do you know
what just happened?

393
00:18:20,692 --> 00:18:23,983
That power couldn't
possibly have come from...

394
00:18:24,067 --> 00:18:26,275
It can't be... [gasps]

395
00:18:27,775 --> 00:18:33,525
[clapping]

396
00:18:33,608 --> 00:18:35,942
[POPE]
Truly remarkable.

397
00:18:37,067 --> 00:18:39,108
[POPE]
You just took Judgment head-on--

398
00:18:39,192 --> 00:18:42,358
an exceedingly
powerful group ritual--

399
00:18:42,442 --> 00:18:44,817
and yet you're still standing.

400
00:18:44,900 --> 00:18:46,233
[NAOFUMI gasps]

401
00:18:46,317 --> 00:18:49,858
[POPE] I'd expect nothing
less from the Shield Hero.

402
00:18:51,817 --> 00:18:53,192
[MELTY]
It's the Pope?!

403
00:18:54,483 --> 00:18:55,900
I know you.

404
00:18:55,983 --> 00:18:57,608
From the cathedral
in the capital!

405
00:18:57,692 --> 00:19:00,692
Oh, so you remember
who I am, do you?

406
00:19:00,775 --> 00:19:04,067
Then surely you're aware
of all your sins, as well.

407
00:19:04,150 --> 00:19:05,608
My sins?

408
00:19:05,692 --> 00:19:07,900
God bestowed holy
water upon you,

409
00:19:07,983 --> 00:19:10,150
and yet you refused
to show Him gratitude

410
00:19:10,233 --> 00:19:12,192
for that most righteous gift.

411
00:19:12,275 --> 00:19:13,817
You also deceived the people

412
00:19:13,900 --> 00:19:16,650
and led them to turn
against their own country.

413
00:19:16,733 --> 00:19:18,150
You must be punished.

414
00:19:18,233 --> 00:19:20,858
I shall purify you
in the name of God.

415
00:19:20,942 --> 00:19:25,233
Your transgressions will
plague this land no more.

416
00:19:25,317 --> 00:19:27,275
[MYNE]
How dare you, Pope Balmus?

417
00:19:27,358 --> 00:19:29,608
Do you realize what
you've just done?!

418
00:19:29,692 --> 00:19:32,108
You very nearly killed the
next queen with that attack,

419
00:19:32,192 --> 00:19:33,983
and the Spear Hero, as well!

420
00:19:34,067 --> 00:19:37,150
The Spear Hero and his party,
including the princess,

421
00:19:37,233 --> 00:19:39,192
were murdered by the
Devil of the Shield.

422
00:19:39,275 --> 00:19:42,192
At least that's the story
the world will be told.

423
00:19:42,275 --> 00:19:46,067
As far as God is concerned,
you're all dead already.

424
00:19:46,150 --> 00:19:47,525
What is this?

425
00:19:47,608 --> 00:19:50,025
Myne, can you explain what
the hell he's talking about?

426
00:19:50,108 --> 00:19:52,692
And if the lives of those who
have been marked for death

427
00:19:52,775 --> 00:19:54,608
do finally come to an end,

428
00:19:54,692 --> 00:19:57,025
that means all is
right with the world.

429
00:19:57,108 --> 00:20:00,983
Everything shall be exactly
as God desires it to be.

430
00:20:01,067 --> 00:20:03,108
This man's completely insane!

431
00:20:03,192 --> 00:20:05,733
That logic's pretty twisted.

432
00:20:05,817 --> 00:20:07,817
Reminds me of someone.

433
00:20:07,900 --> 00:20:09,192
[POPE]
Oh, but don't worry.

434
00:20:09,275 --> 00:20:11,150
We have a plan for
a new government

435
00:20:11,233 --> 00:20:13,775
to take the royal
family's place.

436
00:20:13,858 --> 00:20:15,025
What are you--?!

437
00:20:15,108 --> 00:20:16,442
That's ridiculous!

438
00:20:16,525 --> 00:20:18,692
This country's always
been ruled by royalty.

439
00:20:18,775 --> 00:20:20,442
Our family are the
only ones fit to--

440
00:20:20,525 --> 00:20:23,025
[POPE] Abuse your power
and disrespect the Church?

441
00:20:23,108 --> 00:20:25,608
Look down upon the
apostles of God Himself?

442
00:20:25,692 --> 00:20:27,025
Not anymore.

443
00:20:27,108 --> 00:20:30,567
This country doesn't
need such blasphemy.

444
00:20:31,817 --> 00:20:33,025
[POPE]
Royalty?

445
00:20:33,108 --> 00:20:35,483
You're a pestilence.

446
00:20:35,567 --> 00:20:37,942
And the same applies
to you heroes.

447
00:20:38,025 --> 00:20:39,900
We worship those
who save the world

448
00:20:39,983 --> 00:20:41,358
and its people from the Waves,

449
00:20:41,442 --> 00:20:44,192
but this bunch has done
more harm than good.

450
00:20:44,275 --> 00:20:45,983
For example...

451
00:20:46,067 --> 00:20:49,567
The Spear Hero released a
sealed monster upon the world,

452
00:20:49,650 --> 00:20:51,650
the Sword Hero
caused an epidemic,

453
00:20:51,733 --> 00:20:54,025
and the Bow Hero
ignored his duties,

454
00:20:54,108 --> 00:20:57,150
choosing instead
to serve himself.

455
00:20:57,233 --> 00:20:59,650
Heroes that bring such
devastation to the country

456
00:20:59,733 --> 00:21:01,150
and damage the people's beliefs

457
00:21:01,233 --> 00:21:03,942
are truly nothing
more than imposters.

458
00:21:04,025 --> 00:21:06,275
But... I, uh...

459
00:21:06,358 --> 00:21:08,650
I only did that 'cause
I wanted to help!

460
00:21:08,733 --> 00:21:10,858
Ren and Itsuki were
trying to help, too!

461
00:21:10,942 --> 00:21:13,775
And you think they
were just imposters?!

462
00:21:13,858 --> 00:21:16,858
Your arrogance and
foolishness speak volumes.

463
00:21:16,942 --> 00:21:18,900
Just as theirs did,
when they decided to

464
00:21:18,983 --> 00:21:21,733
investigate matters far
beyond their station.

465
00:21:21,817 --> 00:21:23,275
[NAOFUMI]
Investigating?

466
00:21:23,358 --> 00:21:27,942
Therefore, they forced God's
Judgment to fall upon them.

467
00:21:28,025 --> 00:21:29,942
What are you talking about?

468
00:21:30,025 --> 00:21:32,650
Uh--hey, wait a second!

469
00:21:32,733 --> 00:21:35,192
It wasn't Naofumi?!

470
00:21:35,275 --> 00:21:39,025
[POPE laughs]

471
00:21:39,108 --> 00:21:42,358
This farce has been
entertaining, but that's enough.

472
00:21:46,275 --> 00:21:47,442
[MELTY gasps]

473
00:21:47,525 --> 00:21:50,192
The false Spear Hero and
the Devil of the Shield,

474
00:21:50,275 --> 00:21:53,817
who clings so desperately to
life as if he were a cockroach,

475
00:21:53,900 --> 00:21:57,108
shall be purified
with Holy Judgment.

476
00:21:59,275 --> 00:22:00,525
And this country

477
00:22:00,608 --> 00:22:04,608
shall finally be given
righteous order!

478
00:22:08,233 --> 00:22:10,192
Be careful, Naofumi!

479
00:22:10,275 --> 00:22:12,650
That sword's bad news!

